# Heavy-hardware-only brew bundle. Layered on top of ./Brewfile by the
# install script when the machine's role is one with `heavyHardware = true`
# (currently: role = "mbp"). The Mac mini skips this file entirely.
#
# Manual run:
#   brew bundle install --file=~/dev/dotfiles/Brewfile.heavy

# Local LLM backend (Ollama) for offline / fallback inference.
# Hardware: M5 Max + 128GB unified memory — full SOTA model range available.
# Open Ollama.app once to grant permissions, then see ~/.config/ollama/notes.md
# for env vars and model pulls.
cask "ollama-app"
# Hermes Agent (NousResearch) is Python and ships its own installer that
# provisions uv / Python 3.11 / Node 22 — not on brew. Installed by
# .chezmoiscripts/run_onchange_install-hermes.sh.tmpl on this host.
# Config: dot_hermes/config.yaml.tmpl (cloud-primary, ollama optional).
